a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
c) Emergency stops tested and ready; 
d) Crew vigilance - Constant monitoring of the task; 
e) Sufficient number of crew to be made available; 
f) Any crew not directly involved in mooring operations should stay well clear; 
g) Master to monitor the progress of the operation and crew and to give clear and concise orders; 
h) Winch / windlass must not be left unattended whilst in use; 
i) Ropes must not be used to operate the winch / windlass controls; 
j) Crew should keep clear of all moving parts; 
k) Crew should not stand on or step over mooring lines when made tight.

